 BY
AGNES NWORIE, ABAKALIKI The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, Ebonyi State Command, has intercepted 90,000 litres of suspected adulterated petroleum product in the state. Addressing journalists in Abakaliki, the state capital, on Thursday, the State Commandant of the Corps,  Terrumun Gbue, disclosed that the command also arrested six suspected owners of the adulterated product. The suspects were reportedly nabbed along  the Enugu-Abakaliki Expressway in the night on February 7. According to Gbue, the products were concealed in two vehicles. During interrogation, the suspects could not give any reasonable details of their activities. “We discovered that the way bills attached to the product were fake with one of the articulated vehicles having two way-bills. “All the way bills bore dates in 2021. Investigations are ongoing to get to the root of the matter,” said the commandant. 